Double tread again for this over indulger. Maintaining during the holidays is always a challenge but it’s very simple… more calories in, more calories out. I don’t do a lot of cardio on a regular basis but always do more this time of year. To maintain, you need to burn the same amount of calories that you’re taking in, so if you eat and drink a little more, you add to your workout. Maybe its more cardio, more intensity, heavier weight or maybe you make your workout a bit longer… Doesn’t matter as long as you’re burning more calories. Oh no, I said “burn off”! Stop being offended. It’s the science of calories in vs calories out. It’s not “earning your food” and it’s not a “punishment”. It’s science.

Quick & easy breakfast: baked oatmeal cups!
3 ripe bananas, mashed
3/4 cup oat milk 
1 egg
1tbsp vanilla extract
2 1/4 cups oats
1 tbsp baking powder
1 tbsp cinnamon 
2-3 tbsp honey (depends hose sweet you want it)
Divide into large muffins tin
 Bake on 350° for about 30 min, or until firm.
Refrigerate and eat for breakfast throughout the week!
